The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Fortis in cash chase
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Fortis in cash chase
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, May 21: Hospital chain Fortis Healthcare today said it had successfully completed a $100-million foreign currency convertible bonds (FCCB) issue.         
	The five-year bonds have a yield to maturity of 5.54 per cent and an initial conversion price of Rs 167.         
	Earlier this month, the company had announced plans to raise up to $185 million through a preferential allotment of shares and an FCCB issuance to fund acquisitions.        
	Fortis will raise about $85 million by issuing 22.35 million shares at Rs 170 each on a preferential basis to the private equity and infrastructure arm of Singapores state investment firm, GIC Special Investments Pte Ltd. Religare Capital Markets Plc and The Royal Bank of Scotland were the joint book-runners and lead managers of the issue.                                                                                                                                       
